      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "exploration",
          "intro": "A classic budget explorer fit: maximum FSD, a Guardian booster, fuel scoop, scanner, AFMU and an SRV bay. Initial is the cheapest buy-only floor; A-Rated is the expedition baseline; Engineered maximises jump range and reduces heat — almost entirely range and weight work, with one engineer doing most of it.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Range, scoop, scanner, SRV",
            "text": "The four exploration essentials — a maxed FSD with Guardian booster for range, a class-4 scoop to refuel fast, a Detailed Surface Scanner for mapping payouts, and an SRV bay for exobiology and surface sites. The DBE fits all four with room for a backup AFMU."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Heavy Duty multiplies raw shield strength.",
            "PowerPlant": "4D keeps mass down — with no guns to feed, output is not the limit; Low Emissions cuts heat and draw, Thermal Spread bleeds more for cool scooping.",
            "MainEngines": "4D thrusters; Clean Drive Tuning runs cool for safe planetary work, Stripped Down sheds mass for more jump range.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "The whole build — a 5A drive for maximum range; Increased Range + Mass Manager is the single biggest roll in exploration.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass, Lightweight trims more; life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "4D is plenty without weapons; Engine Focused gives engine-capacitor headroom for repeated boosts climbing out of gravity wells.",
            "Radar": "Drop to D and go Lightweight; exploration needs no sensor range, so save the mass.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock 5C tank; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size4": "Optional / low-priority — Shielded hardens the scoop; scoop rate is unchanged. Refuels from stars.",
            "Slot02_Size4": "The Guardian FSD Booster — a flat jump-range gain unlocked at a Guardian site, not bought; non-negotiable and not engineerable.",
            "Slot03_Size3": "A light SRV hangar (1 bay) for exobiology and Guardian-site runs; under-fills the size-3 slot and carries no blueprint.",
            "Slot04_Size3": "Optional / low-priority — Shielded hardens the AFMU. Repairs modules between fights.",
            "Slot05_Size2": "Enhanced Low Power keeps the shield light and low-draw for the long haul.",
            "Slot06_Size2": "Optional / low-priority — Shielded hardens the AFMU. Repairs modules between fights.",
            "Slot07_Size1": "Optional / low-priority — Expanded Probe Scanning widens probe coverage. Maps planets for exploration data.",
            "Slot08_Size1": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo."
